# Backend development

Before changing Python backend code, read **`backend/docs/BACKEND_GUIDE.md`** (architecture, request flow, modules, conventions).

Also consult:

- `backend/docs/API.md` — endpoint contracts
- `docs/SECURITY.md` — security requirements
- `docs/DEPLOYMENT-AWS.md` — production layout

## Conventions

- Business logic in `service.py` / `auth_service.py`, not in route handlers.
- SQL only in `repository.py` / `auth_repository.py`.
- New env vars: `PS_PRICE_*` prefix, document in `.env.example`.
- Admin features: `admin_routes.py` + `AdminUserDep`, not public endpoints.
